<h1 style="color: darkblue">1. Name the components of html elements properly<h1>
<p> They are defined by a start tag, some content and an end tag. For example <tagname>content<tagname> <p>

<h1 style="color: darkblue">2. Identify void elements and how they are denoted>
<p>Empty elements are usually called void elements and "br" are linebreaks<p>

<h1 style="color: darkblue">3. Identify attributes <h1>
<p>All html Elements can have attributes, they provide additional informationo about elements and are always specified in the start tag.
They usually come in name=value<p>


<h1 style="color: darkblue">4. Write down the correct DOCTYPE declaration for html <h1>
<p> "!DOCTYPE html" <p>

